The Kubernetes scheduler determines the best available node on which to deploy newly created pods. 
If memory swapping is allowed to occur on a host system, this can lead to performance and stability issues within Kubernetes.

To disable the swapoff memory
***Note : To make changes in the fstab file you need sudo privileges.
1.) Use sudo vim /etc/fstab OR go to dir /etc and use sudo vim fstab
2.) Comment off /swap.img line and save the changes in the file by using :wq

3.)If still it shows swapoff memory issue use:
$sudo swapoff -a
